<header class="comment-meta comment-author vcard">
<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/5f9842ec828e5651c53c61299f6362cd?s=44&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/5f9842ec828e5651c53c61299f6362cd?s=88&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' loading='lazy' decoding='async' /><cite><b class="fn">Sarah Bond</b> </cite><a href="https://allaboutcats.com/ginger-cats#comment-37952"><time datetime="2020-02-16T00:35:45+00:00">Feb 16, 2020 at 12:35 am</time></a> </header>
<section class="comment-content comment">
<p>Have a roughly 10 week old ginger girl. Have had her for a month. Others named her Pheonix, I just call her Kittykat. Rescue kitty from bushfires, very sweet, very loving and very scatty. Overly energetic in the morning, including scratching and nipping me, then occassionally chases chickens and ambles through my cattle if they&#8217;re near the house, then sleeps and purrs all day. Just a beautiful little lady. Very happy I reluctantly said ok to taking her. Hubby was not happy, now they are inseparable. :)))</p>
</section>
