<article id="comment-12068" class="comment">
<header class="comment-meta comment-author vcard">
<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/aa8188f3242d97140e0442429d2d1ec7?s=44&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/aa8188f3242d97140e0442429d2d1ec7?s=88&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' loading='lazy' decoding='async' /><cite><b class="fn">Susan Riley</b> </cite><a href="https://allaboutcats.com/ginger-cats#comment-12068"><time datetime="2018-06-27T03:00:30+00:00">Jun 27, 2018 at 3:00 am</time></a> </header>
<section class="comment-content comment">
<p>I have a Jack Russell Shorty who is good friends with my ginger boy. She loves all the cats and I thought it was because she thinks she is a cat. But with a new ginger girl I find they are becoming good buddies as well.</p>
</section>
