<article id="comment-7611" class="comment">
<header class="comment-meta comment-author vcard">
<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/85c9b0c4c69f9f158f0513917af1ec3a?s=44&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/85c9b0c4c69f9f158f0513917af1ec3a?s=88&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' loading='lazy' decoding='async' /><cite><b class="fn">Dorothy Virgadamo</b> </cite><a href="https://allaboutcats.com/ginger-cats#comment-7611"><time datetime="2018-05-02T01:00:31+00:00">May 2, 2018 at 1:00 am</time></a> </header>
<section class="comment-content comment">
<p>I agree with this article. Ginger cats are friendly, affectionate, intelligent, courageous and independent. They are also dog-like and cuddly. I had one Ginger cat for sixteen years. He passed away from old age suddenly. Now I have another Ginger cat. Once you have a Ginger cat, you have a comrade by your side. There is a strong love given by Ginger cats. Once you have a Ginger cat, you will never want any other type of cat. Ginger cats are the best.</p>
</section>
