<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/0dfd3d0fd4dd4de39aaa6b35802b2700?s=44&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/0dfd3d0fd4dd4de39aaa6b35802b2700?s=88&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' loading='lazy' decoding='async' /><cite><b class="fn">Marina King</b> </cite><a href="https://allaboutcats.com/ginger-cats#comment-13873"><time datetime="2018-08-13T17:29:21+00:00">Aug 13, 2018 at 5:29 pm</time></a> </header>
<section class="comment-content comment">
<p>Found nothink about what I was looking for about my ginger and white cat . Were ever he sits he leaves and orange mark and he is the only one of my cats that happens to as my other cats are tabby / brindle.<br />
So why dose my ginger cat do this.?</p>
</section>
<div class="reply">
<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-13873' data-commentid="13873" data-postid="3334" data-belowelement="comment-13873" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Marina King" aria-label='Reply to Marina King'>Reply</a> <span>&darr;</span> </div>
