<ol class="children">
<li class="comment odd alt depth-2" id="li-comment-14707">
<article id="comment-14707" class="comment">
<header class="comment-meta comment-author vcard">
<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/816e40c4145bef96d757c28b3bc55f8a?s=44&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/816e40c4145bef96d757c28b3bc55f8a?s=88&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' loading='lazy' decoding='async' /><cite><b class="fn">Ed.</b> </cite><a href="https://allaboutcats.com/ginger-cats#comment-14707"><time datetime="2018-09-08T00:27:12+00:00">Sep 8, 2018 at 12:27 am</time></a> </header>
<section class="comment-content comment">
<p>Could be scent marking from his anal glands, cats have two glands in this region and they use them to mark territory or an object-saying: this is mine-does he bottom scoot across the floor, lick his behind a lot? If he does then it could be that he is having issues in expressing (releasing) the fluid in them. This is normally done when a cat defecates or is deliberately marking.<br />
Problems can arise so if you are in doubt get him checked over by a vet.</p>
</section>
