<img alt='small mallory photo' src='https://allaboutcats.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/cropped-Small-pfp-44x44.jpg' srcset='https://allaboutcats.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/cropped-Small-pfp-88x88.jpg 2x' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' loading='lazy' decoding='async' /><cite><b class="fn"><a href='https://www.wildernesscat.com/' rel='external nofollow ugc' class='url'>Mallory Crusta</a></b> </cite><a href="https://allaboutcats.com/ginger-cats#comment-47887"><time datetime="2021-03-19T18:47:17+00:00">Mar 19, 2021 at 6:47 pm</time></a> </header>
<section class="comment-content comment">
<p>Hi Julie, it sounds like your cat has a lot of energy and needs good outlets for that desire to play. Make sure that you have plenty of scratchers, appropriate climbing areas, and toys ready for him to use.</p>
</section>
